"""
# Worker Thread

Each worker owns its own EventLoop + IoDriver and handles
thousands of connections via non-blocking I/O. Workers are
spawned by the master HttpServer.

## Architecture

```
Worker Thread
  ├── EventLoop (epoll/kqueue)
  ├── IoDriver (submit/poll completions)
  ├── TcpListener (SO_REUSEPORT, own bind)
  ├── connections: Dict<fd, Connection>
  ├── AsyncRouter
  ├── MiddlewarePipeline
  └── HandlerRegistry
```

## Main Loop

```
while not shutdown:
  1. Check control channel for shutdown/reload
  2. driver.flush()
  3. completions = driver.poll(max_events, timeout_ms)
  4. For each completion: advance connection state machine
  5. Reap expired keepalive connections
```
"""

